While this is correct, we can optimize based on the observation that method definitions are shared between all objects of the same class.
First, note that a method call $	exttt{pet.noise()}$ is syntactic sugar for $	exttt{Pet.noise(pet)}$ (object is passed as parameter). Since $	exttt{noise}$ is not specific to the object $	exttt{pet}$, it can be resolved at compile-time.
. n p n d o e a a a i t m g t s e e a e * c a n t c a a B a m g r t e e e * e d * d o n g d a a B o m g r g e e e * e d * Everytime $	exttt{Pet.noise(pet)}$ is called, just replace it (at compile-time) with the known address of $	exttt{Pet.noise}$ (in our memory model: $	exttt{.data+0x0}$).
For example:
$$  egin{align*} &amp;	exttt{Cat cat}
ewline &amp;	exttt{Dog dog}
